comments.commentBody:
@TDK: I agree with pretty much everything you wrote. The Sweden-Colombia match was also one of the worst for pretty violent play (by the Swedes) tolerated-and it to an extent intimidated the very young Colombian side.<br/>
I guess the general quality of the play has been falling to the level of the refereeing. Totally agree that, in both matches, Norway was bereft of ideas. It's hard to envision them beating the Sheilas. I think a draw is the likely outcome. I really haven't seen any of the teams look convincing for all of their two matches.<br/>
TDK, do you agree that maybe Wambach should sit for a match, if for no other reason than to clear her head? I'd like to see what Cheney and Morgan can do as a pair up top, with Rapinoe and O'Reilly on the wings. I'm just afraid that Sundhage is on the brink of falling into a BB level lack of imagination. At least she cleared out Boxx (for now), so there's hope.
